An abandoned newborn baby was found in Kwa Mashu, Durban on Tuesday. Netcare 911 spokesperson Chris Botha confirmed that paramedics found a newborn baby with the placenta still attached to him in Chakide Road Kwa Mashu. &#8220;The Emergency care Practitioner and the nursing staff cut the cord and placed the baby on oxygen until he was well oxygenated,&#8221; said Botha. The child is currently under the care of the nursing staff until other arrangements are made. Police are investigating the case.&nbsp;-TNA Reporter